headline: Cloud Solution Architect at CDW
summary: IT Professional with 20 years of experience working with Microsoft technologies in many capacities.

experiences.title: Cloud Solution Architect
experiences.description: I help to bridge the gap between a customers business and technical objectives, to cloud solutions on Azure AWS GCP. I am primarily responsible for scoping CDW's Professional and Managed Services engagements.

experiences.title: Customer Success Manager
experiences.description: As a Customer Success Manager, I help customers  successfully define,  implement, and adopt their cloud strategies, focusing on Microsoft cloud technologies.

experiences.title: Microsoft Field Solutions Architect
experiences.description: Technical sales specialist responsible for the sales of Microsoft products and services in southern and central Ohio.

experiences.title: Pilot
experiences.description: I am a member and pilot at The Flying Neutrons flying club in Lebanon, Ohio. Founded in 1952, we are one of the longest running flying clubs in the United States.

experiences.title: Partner Technology Strategist
experiences.description:
I am responsible for developing and enabling cloud practices and capabilities within the Ohio managed partner portfolio. Primarily accomplished by:

     - Training the leadership and sales teams on Microsoft cloud technologies - mainly Office 365 and Azure - and business value conversations
     - Strategizing on next-logical practices to build based on a partners existing capabilities, growth initiatives, and market trends
     - Marketing event planning and coordination as well as speaking at partner led marketing events
     - Customer-facing sales activities with partners (sales calls, envisioning workshops, planning sessions, etc.)
     - Learning path development for technical delivery teams

I also regularly speak at Microsoft-led marketing events and training programs, and have presented to audiences in the hundreds on a wide range of infrastructure and cloud technologies, as well as working with our marketing organization to create and review delivery and demo content.

experiences.title: Server Solution Specialist
experiences.description: I provided technical pre-sales support for the Windows Server platform, virtualization, the System Center Suite, the Forefront suite, and SQL Server to mid-market customers throughout Ohio, Kentucky, and Tennessee. I worked with IT leaders and C-level executives to present the value of Microsoft's server solutions, and engaged partners into opportunities to drive post-sale implementation and deployment conversations.

experiences.title: Professional Services Consultant
experiences.description:
Responsible for the architecture and deployment of Microsoft Exchange 2007 implementations, including migrations from legacy versions of Exchange as well as competitive platforms such as Lotus Notes.

I worked on a 30,000 mailbox Lotus Notes to Exchange migration for a global automotive supplier based out of Detroit. 

I was contracted by Microsoft to write internal process and procedure documentation for their Business Productivity Online Suite (BPOS - the predecessor to Office 365) migration teams based in Winnipeg. Spent 6 weeks in Winnipeg working side by side with migration engineers to refine and document their processes, document internal knowledge base and support articles, and train new migration engineers.

experiences.title: Regional Services Manager
experiences.description:
I relocated to Cincinnati to help launch our new Cincinnati office. Managed the delivery team in our Cincinnati office, consisting of all Microsoft-based Infrastructure, development, and business intelligence consultants. Day to day responsibilities encompassed all operational aspects of the Cincinnati branch including P&L ownership, recruiting, customer satisfaction, employee development / performance management, and resource allocation / scheduling.

I was also the primary technical pre-sales lead for the branch and worked closely with our account executives to position our infrastructure consulting services, author statements of work, and review / approve statements of work that were written by consultants on my team.

experiences.title: Advanced Infrastructure Practice Manager
experiences.description:
Responsible for the operations of the Advanced Infrastructure practice, which designed and deployed Microsoft-based infrastructure solutions as well as Cisco networking technology. Day to day responsibilities included managing on average 20 billable infrastructure consultants, managing the P&L for the practice, recruiting, customer satisfaction, business development, and employee development and performance management.

I was also the primary technical pre-sales resource for the infrastructure practice, wrote the majority of our statements of work, and approved all statements of work written by the infrastructure architects on my team prior to customer delivery.

experiences.title: Principal Consultant
experiences.description: Designed and implemented Microsoft-based infrastructure solutions such as Active Directory, Exchange Server, Systems Management Server (SMS), Microsoft Operations Manager (MOM), and Windows client deployments. Also served in a technical pre-sales capacity, creating work estimates and authoring statements of work.

experiences.title: Senior Systems Engineer
experiences.description:
Designed, deployed, and administered Microsoft Windows NT / 2000, Exchange 5.5 / 2000, and SMS 2.0 environments for organizations throughout southeast Michigan.

I worked on dozens of Microsoft infrastructure projects, troubleshooting calls, and help desk staffing assignments. Billed time at over 100 different customers while in this role.
